Great! I found the pattern. In check-session-archive.mjs, they do:

```javascript
const tmpDir = path.join(ROOT, "tmp", "archive-test-" + Date.now());
mkdirSync(tmpDir, { recursive: true });
const origMemDir = process.env.MEMORY_DIR;
process.env.MEMORY_DIR = tmpDir;
```

So they:
1. Create a temporary directory
2. Save the original MEMORY_DIR
3. Override process.env.MEMORY_DIR BEFORE importing any modules that use config.memoryDir
4. This ensures all config reads use the temp directory

This is the pattern that needs to be applied to the three contaminating scripts.
